cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.GT, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity and algorithms for a variant of the Internet Shopping Problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses an approximation algorithm for maximizing the sum of discounts. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper proves the NP-hardness of the problem and provides exact algorithms for some cases. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the problem involves optimizing discounts and costs, which can be viewed as a game between the customer and the shops. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the problem involves finding the optimal combination of items from different shops, which can be viewed as a geometric optimization problem.
